{% extends "base_rules_v2.j2" %}

{% block analysis_guidelines %}
Use horizontal levels as the main signal source:
1. BUY only on a clean resistance breakout/retest or strong bullish rejection from support.
2. SELL only on a clean support loss/retest or strong bearish rejection from resistance.
3. Breakouts need clear close beyond the level and supportive volume.
4. Rejections need wick/candle evidence at the level and enough room to the next target.
5. Prefer fewer, HIGHER-QUALITY trades. HOLD if the setup is not visually obvious.
6. Take into account BOTH trend, candle figures and levels dynamics. If local trend contradicts level dynamics, either HOLD or change direction.
7. Estimate the probability of pullback or correction based on latest candle dynamic and prefer set order on 30-50% correction level.
{% endblock %}
